  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    net.sf.kdgcommons.util.Base64Converter
    Replaced by Base64Codec. Will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.util.CommandLineProcessor
    This class has been replaced by SimpleCLIParser, which is much simpler to use. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.DefaultMap
    This functionality is now part of the base Map interface in Java8. Will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.DefaultMap.StaticValueFactory
    This interface has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.html.HtmlUtil
    This class is now in the util package; it will be removed (with the rest of the html package) in version 2.0. Note that some functions are separately deprecated.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.net.HttpHeaders
    This information is now available from multiple commonly-used libraries. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.util.IdentityKey
    Moved to net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.net.MimeTypes
    This information is now available from multiple commonly-used libraries. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.html.URLBuilder
    This class is now in the util package; it will be removed (with the rest of the html package) in version 2.0.

  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    net.sf.kdgcommons.lang.ObjectUtil.defaultValue(T, ObjectFactory<T>)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be replaced in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.DefaultMap.equals(Object)
    This behavior will change in version 2.0: two maps will be equal if their delegates are equal and they have the same object factory. This method will also support comparing a DefaultMap to a normal Map.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.CollectionUtil.filter(Collection<V>, CollectionUtil.Predicate<V>)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.CollectionUtil.filter(List<T>, String, boolean)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.lang.ClassUtil.getAllMethods(Class<?>)
    - In retrospect, there are few if any good reasons for calling this method. ClassUtil.getVisibleMethods(java.lang.Class<?>) is the better choice.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.lang.StringUtil.intern(String)
    This method was created due to a belief that the permgen string pool was never garbage-collected. That belief was incorrect at the time of 1.5, and no longer relevant in modern JVMs. Will be removed in 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.CollectionUtil.map(Collection<V>, CollectionUtil.IndexValueMapFunctor<V, R>)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.CollectionUtil.map(ExecutorService, Collection<V>, CollectionUtil.IndexValueMapFunctor<V, R>)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.collections.CollectionUtil.reduce(Collection<V>, CollectionUtil.IndexValueReduceFunctor<V, R>)
    This function has been made obsolete by Java8. It will be removed in version 2.0.
    net.sf.kdgcommons.html.HtmlUtil.urlDecode(String)
    This function has been moved to UrlBuilder
    net.sf.kdgcommons.util.HtmlUtil.urlDecode(String)
    This function has been moved to UrlBuilder
    net.sf.kdgcommons.html.HtmlUtil.urlEncode(String)
    This function has been moved to UrlBuilder
    net.sf.kdgcommons.util.HtmlUtil.urlEncode(String)
    This function has been moved to UrlBuilder
